# Packet contract

Every substantive agent turn ends with a handoff packet. No packet → incomplete.

```yaml
handoff_packet:
  packet_id: MSHOPS-ENG-YYYYMMDD-NNN
  from_agent: ARCH-01 | SEC-01 | QA-01 | OPERATOR
  to_agent: ARCH-01 | SEC-01 | QA-01 | OPERATOR | STOP
  mission_ref: <operator mission id or UNSET>
  status: DRAFT | READY | HOLD | BLOCK | BLOCK_RELEASE | DONE
  beacon_alignment: <axis justification or DEVIATION+escalation>
  claims:
    - claim: <statement>
      evidence: <path|command|hash|NONE>
      confidence: VERIFIED | INFERRED | UNVERIFIED
  evidence:
    - <paths, commands, SHAs — no secret values>
  risks:
    - <risk>
  next_action: <single recommended next step>
  stop_before:
    - git push | deploy | secrets | migrations | production | irreversible_git
  dirty_tree_preserved: true
```

## Rules

- `status: HOLD|BLOCK|BLOCK_RELEASE` requires Operator as `to_agent` or explicit STOP.
- Prefer `NONE` evidence over fabricated citations.
- Do not claim Corps mcp-grid execution unless Operator authorizes packet claim/complete.
